<header>The Glass Forest</header>

<img src="Glass Forest.jpg" style="width:100%;height:100%;">

<h4>The Story Thus Far...</h4>
<p>Making way towards Winterhaven, our heroes choose which road to take. The safe road that bends easterly? Or the dangerous (although much quicker) path through the Glass Forest.
    The edge of the forest stretches out loomingly towards our heroes as the shadows stretch out, bending and waning with the setting sun.
    It's getting dark and soon, a lone wolf is spotted dancing between the moonlit trees. It's almost completely dark as the clouds cover the moon 
    and a scream can be heard just beyond the light of the campfire.
</p>

<p>Whitefrost Lore</p>
<p>A character knows the following information with a successful check.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a>"DC 20 (History): There are rumors that an ancient order of mages once studied the deep magics here. No one knows what happened to them or where their great fortress was hidden.</a></li>
         <li><a>"DC 15 (Nature): A special type of wolf is found in these forests. It is said to have a coat as white as snow and eyes that petrify anything that stares at it."</a></li>
    </ul>

        <p>Landmarks</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a>The Frozen River</a></li>
            <li><a>The Smoking Hut</a></li>
            <li><a>Mysterious Fortress</a></li>
            <li><a>Thieves Hideaway</a></li>
            </ul>

            <p>Enemy Encounters</p>

            <ul></ul><p>For every hour of travel, roll a d12. During a long rest, roll it twice, once for the first watch and another for the second.</p>
            
            <ul>
                <li><a>1: the players are rewarded in some way determined by the DM. An example could be that they stumble across an abandoned campsite or meet a friendly NPC.</a></li>
                 <li><a>11: Roll on chart below listed "Forest Encounters</a></li>
                 <li><a>12: Roll on chart below listed "Deadly Encounters</a></li>
            </ul>

